news.title: Chandigarh administration's court may decide on property tax rates now
news.para: In the past, there were several instances where the Chandigarh administration turned down the MC's plea and passed its own order by reversing the MC's approval.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body house rejects proposal to hike property tax
news.para: The issue was presented in the MC house as mayor Babla allowed the table agenda, proposing increase in property tax in both commercial and residential segments.

news.title: Roads, walls among 80 illegal structures demolished in demolition drive in Gurugram
news.para: Two unauthorized ramps and a gym were demolished at Idea Cosmic Plaza and two offices sealed. Officials, including DTP (enforcement) Amit Madholia and junior engineer Naveen, oversaw the drive.

news.title: Kerala budget 2025-26: Metro rail projects in three cities to get boost
news.para: In his budget speech, the Minister said the existing Kochi Metro line would be extended to more areas in the city, and the proposed Metro projects in Kozhikode and Thiruvananthapuram would become a reality soon.

news.title: Rajasthan Housing Board earns Rs 155.62 crore by selling premium properties
news.para: "We managed to sell 44 out of the 60-odd properties listed in the auction. All these are of premium categories. This shows people have faith in RHB even in premium categories," said housing commissioner Dr Rashmi Sharma.

news.title: NGT forms joint panel to investigate air pollution plaint against ACC cement plant in Himachal Pradesh
news.para: In a recent order, Justice Sudhir Agarwal directed the committee members to visit the cement factory and determine whether the firm had taken necessary measures to contain environmental pollution or there were any violations.

news.title: Over 39.82 lakh houses sanctioned under PMAY-G so far in 2024-25: Government
news.para: ​According to the reply by Minister of State for Rural Development Chandra Sekhar Pemmasani, the ministry had set a target for constructing 84,37,139 houses during 2024-25 in 18 states.

news.title: In a first, Kolkata civic body allows building on 410 sq ft plot
news.para: Construction on such small plots is usually impossible as there is hardly any construction space left if one has to leave open space at the sides, front and rear.

news.title: YEIDA allots four hotel plots near Noida international airport
news.para: The plots, ranging from 3,400-4,000 sqm in Sector 29, received the highest bid of Rs 31 crore. Equasocio Digital Technologies was allotted a 4,000-sqm plot at least Rs 5 crore above its reserve price of Rs 26 crore, officials said.

news.title: Noida authority seals two flats & shop in sector 50 society over Rs 55 crore dues
news.para: It has also approached the district magistrate to recover the pending amount as land revenue. Earlier, it issued multiple cancellation notices to the company on May 7, July 8, and Aug 14 last year.

news.title: Sweden: Skanska operating profit grew 189% in Oct-Dec 2024
news.para: The Nordic region's biggest builder said its operating profit grew 189% on a currency adjusted basis to 2.75 billion Swedish crowns ($252.2 million) in the October-December quarter.

news.title: Average rate on a 30-year mortgage in USA falls to 6.89%
news.para: The average rate fell to 6.89% from 6.95% last week, mortgage buyer Freddie Mac said Thursday. A year ago, it averaged 6.64%.

news.title: TARC posts Rs 29 crore net loss in Q3 FY25
news.para: Total income increased marginally to Rs 11.21 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 10.51 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing on Thursday.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves development authority for Shahjahanpur
news.para: Part of the Bareli administrative division, a survey will be conducted in the 49 revenue villages in Shahjahanpur, which would fall under the jurisdiction of the authority.

news.title: House prices in UK jump by 0.7% in January 2025: Halifax
news.para: House prices climbed by 0.7% in monthly terms last month after falling by 0.2% in December, Halifax said, above a 0.2% increase forecast by economists in a Reuters poll.

news.title: Mumbai: Soon, unmetered properties must pay water, sewage taxes
news.para: According to the Maharashtra govt decision of Feb 2, 2022, residential properties under 500 square feet were exempt from water and sewerage taxes.

news.title: Noida: Developers want to avail rehabilitation policy for five stalled projects
news.para: If YEIDA agrees, officials said, the developers in return will file applications to withdraw cases pending in the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) and in other courts.

news.title: Guntur civic body to focus on bringing more households into tax bracket
news.para: The commissioner found that many residential and commercial buildings were left without imposing property taxes during his field visit and constituted special teams to immediately complete the tax assessment process.

news.title: Titan America raises $384 million in US IPO
news.para: Titan America sold 9 million shares, together with 15 million shares its Belgium-based parent company Titan Cement International offered at $16 apiece. The company had marketed to list its shares in a range of $15-$18 apiece.

news.title: Lucknow development body to organise camp to address map related issues
news.para: The camp aims to process pending map approvals, new map applications, and No Objection Certificates (NOCs) promptly.
